data.description: Here is your chance to live in Money Magazine's Best Place to Live in the US. Easy commute to Nashville either down 1-24 or Highway 12 when the interstate is backed up. Gigabit internet available for remote or hybrid workers. When the day is over, step out into your large park yard surrounded by mature trees and watch the deer and wildlife. Minutes from shopping and Clarksville's downtown area with its rapidly growing selection of restaurants and shopping. This solid brick 3-bedroom 3 bath home has room for a growing family or potential for a mother-in-law apartment in the difficult to find full walk out basement with storm shelter. Very safe, low traffic neighborhood on a dead-end street, and as a bonus a large workshop with electrical and a/c. All this home is waiting for is your touch.
